  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model that predicts pump-induced hemolysis index for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The ML surrogate replaces the full CFD solver for rapid sensitivity sweeps across component-dimension tolerances. COU1 evaluates whether the surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. All 13 credibility factors are addressed; 7 are formally assessed and 6 are scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. Validation results cover nominal in-distribution test-set performance only; one out-of-distribution operating point is noted anecdotally in the narrative and cited as evidence of generalization, but no systematic noise-injection, covariate-shift, or adversarial-perturbation study has been conducted.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
