      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal test-set accuracy — in-distribution hold-out",
      "description": "The ML surrogate was evaluated on a hold-out test set drawn from the same Latin-hypercube design-of-experiments space used for training. Mean absolute error in normalized hemolysis index: 2.3 %. R² = 0.981 across 312 test points. The test set was sampled from the identical flow-speed envelope (1.5–6.0 L/min, 1500–3500 RPM) and component-dimension range used during training; no deliberate distributional shift was introduced. The report notes that one operating point at 6.8 L/min (outside the training envelope) yielded an error of 4.1 %, and the authors state this demonstrates the model 'generalizes well beyond its training domain.' No additional out-of-distribution samples, no noise-injection experiments, and no adversarial perturbation analysis were performed or referenced.",
